Bullet in a Bible (with English. "A bullet in the Bible") â€” the concert CD/DVD disk of the American punk group Green Day which is let out on November 15, 2005. Bullet in a Bible was written down on June 18-19, 2005 during performances of Green Day in Milton Keynes in Great Britain within world tour in support of the last at that time a studio album of American Idiot group. Green Day became headliners of a rock festival which in 2 days was attended by more than 130.000 viewers - the most large audience for group at that time; 14 songs from 20, played by the Californian punks in both days, entered in the track list of Bullet in a Bible. On DVD live recordings alternate with the video topics telling about world round of Green Day in 2005 about fans, about preparation of a concert in Milton Keynes, about visit by musicians of group of the Imperial military of the museum in London. The separate video topic is devoted to each of participants of Green Day.
